----------------------------------------------------------------------
README
----------------------------------------------------------------------

This default example creates an internal mesh with a homogeneous poroelastic medium, with an inviscid fluid.
The model parameters are given by Morency & Tromp (2008), Table 1.


TO RUN:

0. Read the user manual in SPECFEM2D/doc/manual_SPECFEM2D.pdf

1. in SPECFEM2D root directory, configure, e.g. for a serial calculation,
   ./configure FC=gfortran

2. compile:
   make all

3. cd EXAMPLES/poroelastic_infinite_homogeneous

4. execute script to run mesher and solver for P-SV case:
   ./run_this_example.sh

5. check out the output files in the local directory OUTPUT_FILES/

   The seismograms should compare to Fig.4 in Morency and Tromp, Geophys. J. Int. (2008) 175, 301-345.


----------------------------------------------------------------------
